all: Black lives matter.

26:04.171 --> 26:05.781
- Hey, man.

26:05.825 --> 26:07.435
You okay?

26:07.478 --> 26:10.438
- Good.
- How'd it go with IRT?

26:10.481 --> 26:12.440
- Talk to 'em about everything.
- Uh-huh.

26:12.483 --> 26:13.310
- Off the record.

26:13.354 --> 26:14.529
They told me to watch the tape

26:14.573 --> 26:15.704
before I make an official
statement.

26:15.748 --> 26:17.663
- Hmm.

26:17.706 --> 26:19.055
Get any sleep?

26:19.099 --> 26:20.927
- No, not really.

26:20.970 --> 26:24.626
I got a bad taste
on this one, Sarge.

26:24.670 --> 26:27.586
No matter how you slice it,
I got an innocent man killed,

26:27.629 --> 26:29.413
a man who didn't do
a damn thing to deserve it.

26:29.457 --> 26:33.026
- What happened last night
was unfortunate.

26:33.069 --> 26:35.419
- No, it was not unfortunate.

26:35.463 --> 26:37.204
That was murder.

26:37.247 --> 26:39.598
- Well, you haven't seen
the tape, neither have I.

26:40.990 --> 26:42.296
- What are you saying?

26:42.339 --> 26:44.254
- I'm saying I'm not ready to
accuse a cop,

26:44.298 --> 26:46.648
one of our own, of murder
until I know all the facts.

26:46.692 --> 26:50.086
- That cop ain't one of us,
Sarge.

26:50.130 --> 26:51.697
- Yeah, maybe.

26:53.568 --> 26:54.482
I'll tell you what,

26:54.525 --> 26:56.310
Daryl definitely ain't
one of us.

26:56.353 --> 27:00.140
That is a stone-cold criminal,
puts bodies on the street,

27:00.183 --> 27:01.837
gets young kids
hooked on heroin.

27:01.881 --> 27:05.580
- He wasn't being a criminal
when he got shot.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.190
That's the point.

27:14.328 --> 27:17.026
- Kelton's blaming you for
what happened to Daryl.

27:17.070 --> 27:19.289
Thinks you should have
identified yourself

27:19.333 --> 27:21.988
as a police officer to
deescalate the situation.

27:22.031 --> 27:24.512
- Unbelievable.
- Mm-hmm.

27:24.555 --> 27:26.427
Mm-hmm.

27:26.470 --> 27:29.343
- After all of this
I'm the bad guy.

27:29.386 --> 27:30.997
Sarge, you know that Kelton
doesn't care about

27:31.040 --> 27:32.563
a damn thing,
but that election.

27:32.607 --> 27:34.740
- Yeah, I know that.

27:34.783 --> 27:37.830
But it doesn't matter.

27:37.873 --> 27:39.614
But if we bust Gamble,

27:39.658 --> 27:42.704
we give Kelton something to
talk about, to brag about.

27:44.880 --> 27:46.186
- That dirties Daryl,

27:46.229 --> 27:47.666
makes the whole situation
less tragic.

27:47.709 --> 27:49.624
- Uh-huh, yeah, that too.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.235
Well, let's face it.

27:52.279 --> 27:56.065
There is no easy answer
on this; there just isn't.

28:00.722 --> 28:03.725
- Let's finish this thing then.
- Good.

28:03.769 --> 28:07.033
So, go pay your respects
to Daryl's family.

28:07.076 --> 28:08.425
- What?

28:08.469 --> 28:11.820
- Go to his aunt's house,
connect with Gamble,

28:11.864 --> 28:14.954
and close that heroin deal
with him instead of Daryl.

28:29.098 --> 28:30.839
- Laz.
- Hey, yo.

28:30.883 --> 28:32.449
What up, Kev?

28:33.929 --> 28:35.757
- Did what I could do.

28:35.801 --> 28:37.498
- Appreciate you.

28:37.541 --> 28:39.630
- All right.
- Come on in.

28:41.763 --> 28:44.766
- Hi.
- Thank you for coming.

28:44.810 --> 28:47.900
- Thank you for having me,
Mama Donna.

28:57.039 --> 29:01.609
Vance...I'm sorry, bro.

29:01.652 --> 29:04.177
I did the best I could
to help him, it got crazy.

29:04.220 --> 29:06.788
- Right.

29:10.705 --> 29:13.795
- I didn't know Daryl
that well...

29:13.839 --> 29:17.712
But I do know he loved you.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.935
Hey, your brother didn't smile
that much, man,

29:22.978 --> 29:25.981
but every time I brought
you up...

29:26.025 --> 29:29.158
He smiled with pride.

29:30.420 --> 29:34.598
That's all it was, pure pride.

29:37.166 --> 29:41.649
- Vance, your ti-ti
needs you, man.

29:41.692 --> 29:43.651
- Go be strong.

29:48.743 --> 29:50.005
- You got it, man.

29:57.883 --> 29:59.536
They were sweating us
for no reason,

29:59.580 --> 30:01.756
and then a robbery call
came over the radio.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.498
And they really went crazy,
like that justified everything

30:04.541 --> 30:06.805
they wanted to do to us
in the first place.

30:06.848 --> 30:08.328
- Same ol' song, man.

30:08.371 --> 30:11.070
- You know how it goes,
trying to provoke us.

30:11.113 --> 30:13.376
I think Daryl caught onto that
before I did, which...

30:13.420 --> 30:17.641
made him
get aggressive and...

30:17.685 --> 30:20.383
did what he did, you know?

30:22.037 --> 30:24.126
- I loved Daryl, man,

30:24.170 --> 30:26.346
like he was my own flesh
and blood.

30:30.219 --> 30:33.614
He gone now, so...life goes on.

30:35.094 --> 30:38.880
It ain't right.
It just is what it is.

30:38.924 --> 30:40.664
- Yeah.

30:40.708 --> 30:42.884
Life does go on.

30:42.928 --> 30:46.409
So, in that spirit,
Daryl did put down 20%

30:46.453 --> 30:48.759
on a buy that was supposed
to get done that night.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.460
Talked to my homie, Tony,
you can have your money back

30:53.503 --> 30:55.070
or proceed with
the transaction.

30:55.114 --> 30:56.593
It's up to you.

30:57.768 --> 31:01.816
- Yo, Kev, you're all about
business, huh?

31:01.860 --> 31:03.687
I like that.

31:05.951 --> 31:07.909
- So, what do you want me
to tell Tony?

31:13.306 --> 31:15.047
- You know what?

31:15.090 --> 31:16.744
Set it up.
- All right.

31:16.787 --> 31:19.181
Gotchu.
- Let me know.

31:27.363 --> 31:29.191
- Mm.

31:29.235 --> 31:31.411
- It's the best in the Midwest.

31:33.804 --> 31:36.720
- Let the street decide that,
eh?

31:36.764 --> 31:38.897
This is you.

31:38.940 --> 31:39.985
- Okay.

31:40.028 --> 31:41.508
- It's good doing business
with you.

31:41.551 --> 31:43.379
- You two leave out the back.
- Yeah.

31:43.423 --> 31:44.772
That's good business, man.

31:44.815 --> 31:46.078
Now that's how we do it.
I see you.

31:46.121 --> 31:47.514
I see you, baby.

31:47.557 --> 31:49.429
- Chicago PD, don't move.

31:50.169 --> 31:51.692
- Freeze!

31:51.735 --> 31:53.085
Drop the bag,
hands in the air.

31:53.128 --> 31:54.477
- Whoa.

31:55.261 --> 31:57.219
- Against the car.

31:57.263 --> 31:59.613
- Oh, you lying son of a bitch.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.571
You set Daryl up, huh?

32:01.615 --> 32:04.096
You got him killed?

32:04.139 --> 32:06.881
Man, how you gonna do this to
your own people, man?

32:06.925 --> 32:09.362
You're worse than the cop
that pulled the trigger, Kev.

32:09.405 --> 32:11.146
I see you.

32:12.060 --> 32:15.411
- Hey, great work, Kev.
We got him.

32:15.455 --> 32:16.673
- Yeah, we got him.

32:16.717 --> 32:19.502
That's all that matters,
getting him,

32:19.546 --> 32:21.678
no matter what it costs.

32:56.191 --> 32:58.150
- You okay?

33:01.240 --> 33:03.111
- So, what do you think?

33:04.199 --> 33:06.810
- Just trying to sort it
all out, man.

33:06.854 --> 33:08.987
- Is the video helping
or hurting?

33:14.340 --> 33:17.996
- The video can't hear what
the punk ass cop was saying.

33:18.039 --> 33:19.258
I blinked the wrong way,

33:19.301 --> 33:21.390
that white boy would have
shot me.

33:21.434 --> 33:23.131
Killed me dead.
I mean, you look at the video.

33:23.175 --> 33:25.003
Maybe Daryl is lunging
for the cop's gun,

33:25.046 --> 33:27.092
but it should
have never got that far.

33:28.354 --> 33:30.138
- Mm-hmm.

33:34.360 --> 33:37.145
I'm glad you didn't blink
the wrong way.

33:39.104 --> 33:41.236
Look, I know you're gonna be
under a lot of pressure

33:41.280 --> 33:44.196
to do the right thing
from your community,

33:44.239 --> 33:46.676
your friends, your family.

33:46.720 --> 33:49.157
Police, on the other side,
they expect you to act

33:49.201 --> 33:51.551
a certain way,
back up your fellow officer.

33:51.594 --> 33:53.074
- Where do you stand?

33:55.598 --> 33:59.254
- It's tough to say,
because I'm white.

34:00.603 --> 34:03.345
And no matter how hard I try
or how badly I wanna understand

34:03.389 --> 34:07.219
what just happened,
what you just experienced,

34:07.262 --> 34:08.655
I can't.

34:11.049 --> 34:12.615
I never will.

34:16.402 --> 34:19.274
But I got your back, always.

34:21.015 --> 34:22.582
Either way, I got your back.

34:24.366 --> 34:28.501
- Thanks a lot.
Needed that.

34:44.430 --> 34:46.258
Hello?

34:48.912 --> 34:51.393
Okay, I'll be there.

34:51.437 --> 34:54.744
- Congratulations on
taking down Phil Gamble.

34:54.788 --> 34:56.833
Ooh, that son of a bitch
has been

34:56.877 --> 34:58.270
a pain in my ass for years.

34:58.313 --> 35:00.707
- Well, I'm glad we can help.
- Mm-hmm.

35:00.750 --> 35:03.362
- I'm assuming that's not why
you called me down here.

35:04.841 --> 35:07.366
- No.

35:09.019 --> 35:11.544
I wanna talk to you about
the police shooting.

35:13.198 --> 35:16.897
Your statement will carry
a lot of weight...

35:16.940 --> 35:19.813
will add lots of
important context to

35:19.856 --> 35:21.249
a complicated situation.

35:21.293 --> 35:25.819
So, as you begin to sort
through things,

35:25.862 --> 35:27.864
I wanna make sure
you feel protected.

35:27.908 --> 35:29.605
- Protected from what?

35:29.649 --> 35:33.261
- The truth, your truth...

35:33.305 --> 35:37.004
Whether or not it actually is
the truth.

35:37.047 --> 35:38.440
- You're asking me to lie?

35:38.484 --> 35:40.703
- No, I'm asking you
to be strong.

35:40.747 --> 35:43.532
To do what's necessary to
punish these racist punks

35:43.576 --> 35:46.056
who killed one of our own
for no reason.

35:51.758 --> 35:53.151
- Good to see you again, Ray.

35:53.194 --> 35:54.456
- Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait.

35:54.500 --> 35:56.154
- Why is it so important
to you?

35:56.197 --> 35:57.155
You the one who told us to go
after Daryl

35:57.198 --> 35:58.634
in the first place.

35:58.678 --> 36:00.070
Thought you couldn't stand
his ass, remember?

36:00.114 --> 36:01.637
- I did.

36:01.681 --> 36:04.988
And the truth is, I don't give
a damn about his death.

36:05.032 --> 36:07.469
But I do care about a white cop

36:07.513 --> 36:09.602
killing a black man for
no reason.

36:14.215 --> 36:15.738
- There's a video out there
that shows

36:15.782 --> 36:18.001
Daryl lunging for that gun.

36:18.045 --> 36:19.351
It's tough to get around.

36:19.394 --> 36:21.048
- You don't have to worry about
none of that.

36:21.091 --> 36:23.093
You just speak your piece.

36:24.182 --> 36:27.663
I've done research on this cop,
Doyle.

36:27.707 --> 36:29.230
He's got a track record.

36:29.274 --> 36:33.103
He's been written up for
using the 'N' word before.

36:33.147 --> 36:35.802
So, you are gonna
tell COPA that

36:35.845 --> 36:38.935
you heard him use the word,

36:38.979 --> 36:40.328
that he told his partner
he was gonna

36:40.372 --> 36:41.677
"take care of those black boys"

36:41.721 --> 36:43.853
the second he got out of
his patrol car.

36:43.897 --> 36:45.551
And we'll be fine.

36:45.594 --> 36:49.511
We'll have intent, nullify that
video you're worried about.

36:49.555 --> 36:53.298
This isn't about you anymore,
Kevin.

36:55.474 --> 36:58.128
This is about
the future of Chicago.

36:58.172 --> 36:59.956
- Future of Chicago?

37:00.000 --> 37:01.784
- Mm-hmm.

37:04.526 --> 37:07.399
I've decided I'm gonna run
for Mayor.

37:10.880 --> 37:13.709
And this is the thing
that's gonna get us elected.

37:30.465 --> 37:32.250
- Got a call from COPA.

37:35.078 --> 37:37.603
They wanna talk to you today.

37:39.779 --> 37:43.130
- That's fine.

37:48.614 --> 37:50.746
- You all set?

37:54.837 --> 37:58.145
Look, I know you got people
talking in both your ears.

38:01.714 --> 38:04.630
You gotta do what you think
is right.

38:07.285 --> 38:12.115
Just...just keep in mind
you're a cop.

38:15.684 --> 38:19.253
That's what you get paid for,
not to change the world.

38:22.082 --> 38:26.042
- I just thought that's what
we were supposed to do...

38:26.086 --> 38:28.175
make the world better.

38:30.482 --> 38:35.225
- Just...remember
this is Chicago.

38:37.184 --> 38:39.360
It's not easy to be
an idealist.

38:51.503 --> 38:53.505
- Officer Atwater,
please tell us what

38:53.548 --> 38:56.638
you witnessed the night of
February 5th.

39:04.603 --> 39:06.822
- How you doing?
- What's up, man?

39:16.441 --> 39:17.659
- What the hell are you
doing here?

39:17.703 --> 39:19.400
- I talked to COPA today.
- Yeah, so what?

39:19.444 --> 39:21.576
You're coming down here--
you're gonna brag about it?

39:21.620 --> 39:24.362
- I told 'em it was
a good shoot.

39:28.453 --> 39:32.021
You?

39:32.065 --> 39:33.806
You backed me?

39:33.849 --> 39:37.375
- I told the truth.

39:41.422 --> 39:43.381
- I appreciate that, bro.

39:43.424 --> 39:45.383
- Don't call me "bro."

39:54.174 --> 39:57.525
No, I didn't come down here
to shake hands and make up.

39:59.397 --> 40:02.530
- Oh.
So it's like that, huh?

40:02.574 --> 40:05.925
- Yeah, it's like that.

40:05.968 --> 40:07.840
Let's go.

40:21.810 --> 40:23.421
Hey, look, man,
we don't gotta do this.

40:23.464 --> 40:24.422
- Oh.

40:37.522 --> 40:39.306
- You put a gun to my head.

40:40.612 --> 40:42.744
Hey, you might not go down
for that murder,

40:42.788 --> 40:44.790
but I will get your badge
one way or the other.

40:55.627 --> 40:57.498
- How does that feel?

40:57.542 --> 40:59.761
Huh?

40:59.805 --> 41:02.851
- Feel like a man?
Huh, boy?
